"title": "4812: darkness, and God's judgment",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4812",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Darkness is used figuratively of God's present and final judgment upon individuals, unfaithful Israel and the heathen nations.</p>\n<h2>Darkness as a symbol of judgment upon ungodly individuals</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:30\">MAT 25:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:9-1Sam2:10\">1SA 2:9–2:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job5:13-Job5:14\">JOB 5:13–5:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job12:25\">JOB 12:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job15:22-Job15:23\">JOB 15:22–15:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job15:30\">JOB 15:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job18:5-Job18:6\">JOB 18:5–18:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job18:18\">JOB 18:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job20:24-Job20:26\">JOB 20:24–20:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job22:10-Job22:11\">JOB 22:10–22:11</a> <em>Eliphaz reasons on the assumption that Job's suffering proves his wickedness</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps35:5-Ps35:6\">PSA 35:5–35:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa8:22\">ISA 8:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:11-Jer23:12\">JER 23:11–23:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:13\">MAT 22:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:17\">2PE 2:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:13\">JUD 1:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev16:10-Rev16:11\">REV 16:10–16:11</a></p>\n<h2>Darkness as a symbol of judgment upon unfaithful Israel</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:28-Deut28:29\">DEU 28:28–28:29</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:29-Isa5:30\">ISA 5:29–5:30</a></strong> <em>This will be fulfilled at the time of Israel's captivity.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:9-Isa59:10\">ISA 59:9–59:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:10\">ROM 11:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer4:27-Jer4:28\">JER 4:27–4:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer13:16\">JER 13:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:2\">LAM 3:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:6\">LAM 3:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:12\">MAT 8:12</a></p>\n<h2>Darkness as a symbol of judgment upon heathen nations</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa47:5-Isa47:7\">ISA 47:5–47:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek30:18\">EZK 30:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek32:7-Ezek32:8\">EZK 32:7–32:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah1:8\">NAM 1:8</a></p>\n<h2>Darkness as a symbol of judgment at the day of the Lord</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:31\">JOL 2:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa13:9-Isa13:10\">ISA 13:9–13:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa34:4\">ISA 34:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:1-Joel2:2\">JOL 2:1–2:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:10\">JOL 2:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel3:14-Joel3:15\">JOL 3:14–3:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:18-Amos5:20\">AMO 5:18–5:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos8:9\">AMO 8:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph1:14-Zeph1:15\">ZEP 1:14–1:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech14:6\">ZEC 14:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:29\">MAT 24:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:19-Acts2:20\">ACT 2:19–2:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:1-1Thess5:3\">1TH 5:1–5:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev6:12-Rev6:17\">REV 6:12–6:17</a></p>",
